INSERT INTO maxims (source, principle, naive_reading, master_reading) VALUES
('Sun Tzu','All warfare is based on deception.','Lie to everyone about everything.','Control what you reveal. Never broadcast your plans, weaknesses, or timing. Formlessness is defense, not fraud.'),
('Sun Tzu','Supreme excellence: subdue the enemy without fighting.','Avoid all confrontation; be passive.','Position and prepare so overwhelmingly that most fights become unnecessary. Win in the setup, not the clash.'),
('Sun Tzu','Know the enemy and know yourself; in a hundred battles you will never be in peril.','Spy on people.','Ruthless self-audit first (the debrief), then honest study of the terrain and the opposition. Most people know neither.'),
('Sun Tzu','The victorious warrior wins first and then goes to war.','Only fight when victory is guaranteed - so never risk anything.','Preparation IS the battle. Exams, interviews, negotiations are decided in the weeks before, not in the room.'),
('Sun Tzu','Be formless, like water.','Have no principles or identity.','Fixed principles, flexible tactics. Adapt method to terrain while your core laws stay constant.'),
('Sun Tzu','Speed is the essence of war.','Rush everything.','A good plan executed now beats a perfect plan executed never. Momentum compounds; delay bleeds supplies.'),
('Sun Tzu','No leader should put troops into the field merely to gratify his own spleen.','Suppress all emotion forever.','Never make irreversible moves while hot. Anger passes; sent messages and burned bridges do not.'),
('Sun Tzu','Foreknowledge comes only from men who know.','Manipulate insiders for information.','Ask people one step ahead of you. Mentors and books are legal espionage. Guessing is expensive; asking is cheap.'),
('Machiavelli','Everyone sees what you appear to be, few experience what you really are.','Fake everything; wear masks.','Your image is real strategic terrain. Manage it honestly: display your competence deliberately instead of hoping it gets noticed.'),
('Machiavelli','It is better to be feared than loved, if you cannot be both.','Intimidate and threaten people.','Be respected: predictable standards, enforced boundaries, consequences that are calm and certain. Fear here = taken seriously.'),
('Machiavelli','A prince must avoid being hated above all things.','Just don''t get caught.','The master constraint governing every tactic. Detected manipulation = hatred = long-term destruction. This is why manipulators lose.'),
('Machiavelli','One must be a fox to recognize traps, and a lion to frighten wolves.','Set traps (fox) and attack people (lion).','Fox = SEE manipulation coming. Lion = be costly to attack. Both are defensive postures that make you a hard target.'),
('Machiavelli','He who neglects what is done for what ought to be done effects his ruin.','Morality is for suckers.','Strategize for the world as it IS. People act on incentives; plan for that reality while keeping your own code.'),
('Machiavelli','Fortune is a river; build dikes and dams in calm weather.','Luck doesn''t exist.','You cannot control events, but preparation shrinks luck''s territory. Build systems before the flood, not during.'),
('Machiavelli','Whoever causes another to become powerful ruins himself.','Never help anyone.','Do not build your position on a single patron, platform, or person who can withdraw it. Own your foundations.'),
('Machiavelli','Never outsource your arms; mercenaries are useless and dangerous.','Trust no one to do anything.','Never rent your CORE capability. Skills central to your survival must be owned, trained in-house, daily.'),
('Machiavelli','The people are more constant and wiser than princes. (Discourses)','Follow the crowd.','Good systems (orders) outperform brilliant moods. Trust your constitution - laws, routines, reviews - over daily feelings.'),
('Machiavelli','Return to beginnings, or corruption completes itself. (Discourses)','Nostalgia is strategy.','All systems decay silently. Scheduled renewal - weekly reviews, re-reading your founding laws - is maintenance of power.'),
('Musashi','You can only fight the way you practice.','Practice fighting.','Your daily conduct IS your performance. Sloppy practice days build a sloppy operator. Train like it counts, because it does.'),
('Musashi','Do nothing which is of no use.','Never rest or have fun.','Rest and scheduled entertainment ARE useful - they are recovery. The useless is the unscheduled leak: doomscrolling, drifting, dithering.'),
('Clausewitz','Everything is very simple in war, but the simplest thing is difficult. (Friction)','Plans are pointless.','Plans degrade on contact with reality - so build 20% buffer, expect friction, and never interpret friction as personal failure.'),
('Clausewitz','Every offensive weakens as it advances. (Culminating point)','Always stop early.','Know when pushing further destroys gains: the 10th study hour, the argument won too hard, the workout past form. Stop at the peak.'),
('Stoic','It is not events that disturb us, but our opinions about events. (Epictetus)','Nothing matters; feel nothing.','Between event and response there is a judgment - and the judgment is yours. That gap is where all your power lives.'),
('Stoic','We suffer more in imagination than in reality. (Seneca)','Never plan for problems.','Plan for problems, then stop rehearsing them. Preparation once; anxiety on repeat is paying interest on a debt you may never owe.'),
('Stoic','The obstacle is the way. (Marcus Aurelius)','Seek out suffering.','Every blocked path trains something: patience, creativity, strength. Ask of each obstacle: what is this making me practice?'),
('Greene','Never outshine the master. (Law 1)','Hide your talent forever.','Read the room and the hierarchy. Display competence in ways that make allies of the powerful, not threatened enemies. DEFENSE: notice when others manage YOU this way.');
